HTTP (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol):
HTTP is a web-based protocol used for communication between client and server.
Communication happens between a web browser & client.
HTTP Response / Request cycle: If we make a request ←→ You will get a Response.
Protocol → A protocol is a collection of rules that will allow two systems to communicate.
By using networking protocols, the computer & server share instructions to understand each other.
On the Web, the protocol used is known as HTTP.

