Page 2: HTTP Workflow & Drawbacks
Workflow Diagram:
Web browser / Client sends a Request through the Internet, which is then sent to the Webserver.
The Webserver sends a Response back through the Internet to the Web browser / Client.
Flowchart:
User will interact with the web browser.
Web browser will send the request to a server via HTTP.
It travels through the Internet and reaches the webserver.
Webserver responds to the web browser via HTTP.
Through this process, an HTTP request will retrieve Pages, Pictures, and Videos.
Note on Drawbacks:
HTTP has a major flaw: It transmits data and information in plaintext.
If anyone intercepts the connection, they can literally read exactly what is being sent or received.
As the internet evolves, everyone depends on the web for:
Personal communication
Bank accounts
Social media
Ecommerce
This lack of privacy has made security a significant concern.

