Page 4: HTTP Request & Response Structure
Browser Indicators:
HTTPS → The browser provides a "Host certificate" (lock icon).
HTTP → The browser displays a "Not secure" message.
HTTPS is internationally approved; browsers like Chrome and Edge prioritise it.
SEO Benefit: Search engines show HTTPS sites at the top of search results.
HTTP Request Structure:
Contains the request sent from the client browser to the webserver.
Components:
Method (e.g., GET)
URL
HEADER (e.g., HOST: example.com)
BODY
Example: GET /api/user HTTP/1.1
HTTP Response Structure:
Contains the response sent from the webserver to the client browser.
Components:
Status code (e.g., 200 OK)
Header
Body (JSON) (e.g., Content-Type: application/json)

