Page 5: HTTP Methods & Status Codes
HTTP Methods:
GET: Used to fetch data from the webserver.
POST & PUT: Used to create & update resources.
POST → Used to create content.
PUT → Used to update existing data.
DELETE → Used to delete data.
Method Categorisation:
Safe Method: GET (It results in no updates to the webserver).
Unsafe Method / Idempotent: POST, DELETE, PUT (These will update the data on a webserver).
HTTP Status Codes: These are responses given by the server back to the client:
200 ⇒ Successful
201 ⇒ Created
204 ⇒ No content (Accidental sent, please delete)
400 ⇒ Client mistake
401 ⇒ Unauthorized access
403 ⇒ Forbidden (No entry)
404 ⇒ Not found (Page not found)
429 ⇒ Too many requests
500 ⇒ Internal Server Error
